flowRoot.flowPara: APT-GET stands for Advanced Packaging Tool and is like an installer, it simplifies the installation of programs on the Debian Linux Distribution (Not Windows or MAC) computers.
An encrypted troop is a troop that can be hidden. Any troop can be encrypted. To make an encrypted troop use RSA (refer to RSA in Buildings).

A Handshake is agreement between two parties. Agreements are connections between two parties, thus Handshake is a connection between two entities. Use handshake to make connections or paths between two location.
Have you ever installed a program on your computer? Installer works the same way, it lets you install(put) buildings on a location in your network.

Spoof functions similarly to a spoof attack. A spoof attack is where a malicious outsider on a network masquerades as someone else to gain some type of advantage. Spoof in the game will build a fake building. Use Spoof to trick the enemy into attacking a fake building.

Ping is a computer network tool that is used to test whether a computer is reachable on a network through its communication channels. Cool fact: Ping is named after the actual sound of sonar (echolocation). Like Sonar ping locates. Use it to locate the enemy.
